Blog: http://new2jquery.com/jquery/tipitup-jquery-image-tooltip

Demo page: http://new2jquery.com/wp-content/demos/TipItUp/index.html


Using the plugin: 

All you have to do to use this plugin is select the element that contains a set of links which link to image files.

For example:
------------

<div class="thumbs">
    
    <a href="/path_to_image/filename.jpg" title="This is the image title">

</div>

----------

Add a tooltip to show the image like this:

----------

$(function() {
    $('.thumbs').TipItUp();

    // customize options support:
    $('.thumbs').TipItUp({
        offset: 20; // offset from mouse position
        speed: 50; // fade in speed
        delay: 100; // delay before fade in
    });
});

----------
Using the style option
----------

$(function() {
    $('.thumbs').TipItUp({
	style : {
		border: "1px solid #999",
		backgroundColor: "green",
		color: "white",
		padding: "10px",
		fontWeight: "bold"
	}

    });
});




Changelog:

 * Version 1.0.4
   Added new options for removeHref, removeTitle, styles, offsetx and offsety.
   The options for offsetx and offsety are still buggy and need fixing. Recommend not using these yet.

 * Version 1.0.3
   First working production version.